## Algorithm 1: Online Adaptive MPC-ICCBF

Given: $\boldsymbol{\alpha}_{0}^{*}$ : Initial class $\mathcal{K}$ functions; $\pi_{i, 1}$ : MPC-ICCBF controller;
F: PENN model with trained parameters $\boldsymbol{\theta}_{1: B}$;
for $t=1, \ldots, T_{\max }$ do
$\boldsymbol{x}_{t}, \mathcal{E}_{t} \leftarrow$ Sensor();
$\mathfrak{A}_{\text {cand }}=\left\{\boldsymbol{\alpha}^{(k)}\right\}_{k=1}^{K} \leftarrow$ SampleCandidates $\left(\boldsymbol{\alpha}_{t-1}^{*}\right)$;
$\mathbf{X}=\left\{X^{(k)}\right\}_{k=1}^{K} \leftarrow$ CreateInputs $\left(\boldsymbol{x}_{t}, \mathcal{E}_{t}, \mathfrak{A}_{\text {cand }}\right)$;
$\mathfrak{E}, \overline{\mathbf{Y}}=\left\{\hat{Y}^{(k)}\right\}_{k=1}^{K} \leftarrow \mathbf{F}\left(\mathbf{X} ; \boldsymbol{\theta}_{1: B}\right)$;
$\mathfrak{A}_{\text {valid }}=\left\{\boldsymbol{\alpha}: D(\bar{X} ; \mathfrak{E})<D_{\text {thr }}\right.$
$\wedge \sup _{\mathbf{E}_{b} \in \mathfrak{E}} \operatorname{CVaR}_{\epsilon}^{\mathbf{E}_{b}(X)}(\bar{\phi}) \leq \bar{\phi}\}$;
$\boldsymbol{\alpha}_{t}^{*} \leftarrow \arg \min _{\boldsymbol{\alpha} \in \mathfrak{A}_{\text {valid }}} \hat{\delta}$;
$\boldsymbol{u}_{t} \leftarrow \pi_{\boldsymbol{\alpha}_{t}^{*}}\left(\boldsymbol{x}_{t}\right)$
ApplyControlInput $\left(\boldsymbol{u}_{t}\right)$;
